OL,3,CBristol mother died after tripping on
OL,4,C'metal flap' outside hospital
OL,6,F"The trip hazard wasn't known about
OL,7,Fand not actioned upon. There was no
OL,8,Fsystem to manage these bollards. It
OL,9,Fshould have been padlocked.
OL,11,F"Standard operating procedures have
OL,12,Fchanged now. Monthly inspections have
OL,13,Fbeen added to the system. There are
OL,14,Fchecks to make sure padlocks don't
OL,15,Fcome off again."
OL,17,FThe inquest heard Lorna developed
OL,18,Fpneumonia after her operation which,
OL,19,Fconsultant Alastair Kiszely explained,
OL,20,Fshe was 'understandably concerned'
OL,21,Fabout.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
